    user_response: "# Task name\n\n**OpenCode Web UI \342\200\224 Frontend Phase 1A: Production Shell and Interaction Foundation**\n\n## To me\n\n1. Paste this entire instruction into Google AI Studio.\n2. Give the builder access to the existing repository if supported.\n3. Do not ask it to build the complete application.\n4. Do not allow it to add Fastify, OpenCode SDK integration, SSE, WebContainers, preview processes, authentication, or real API calls in this task.\n5. Review the complete file batch before accepting it.\n6. The task is complete only when the final score is at least **9/10** and all available frontend gates pass.\n\n---\n\n# To dev\n\nImplement **Frontend Phase 1A only**.\n\nThis is a bounded frontend foundation slice for the OpenCode Headless Web UI. Build a polished, production-quality Vite React shell that later phases can connect to the Fastify gateway and OpenCode runtime.\n\nDo not implement Phase 2 or any backend-dependent functionality.\n\n## Atomic delivery rules\n\nBefore writing code:\n\n1. Inspect the existing repository structure.\n2. Detect the existing package manager from the repository configuration and lockfiles.\n3. List every file you will create or modify.\n4. Keep the batch small enough that every file can be emitted completely.\n5. Confirm that no file will be truncated.\n6. Do not begin a file that cannot be completed in the current response.\n\nDuring implementation:\n\n* Provide complete files.\n* Do not use placeholder comments.\n* Do not write `TODO` in place of required behaviour.\n* Do not claim a file was created unless its full content is provided or it was actually written in the repository.\n* Do not introduce backend APIs or invent OpenCode response shapes.\n* Do not start the next slice.\n\nAfter implementation:\n\n* Run all available frontend checks.\n* Update `IMPLEMENTATION_MANIFEST.md`.\n* Report exact command results.\n* Commit and push only when every required gate passes.\n* If repository execution is unavailable, output the complete files and clearly mark commands as not executed.\n\n---\n\n# Objective\n\nCreate the frontend application foundation with:\n\n* Vite\n* React\n* TypeScript\n* React Router\n* Tailwind CSS\n* Zustand\n* Lucide icons\n* Accessible reusable UI primitives\n* Responsive three-panel application shell\n* Mock data isolated from production state\n* Loading, empty, degraded, and error states\n* Dark and light appearance support\n* Keyboard-accessible navigation\n* Initial frontend tests\n\nThe UI should feel similar to a professional AI development workspace, not a generic dashboard template.\n\n---\n\n# Required visual structure\n\nBuild this desktop layout:\n\n```text\n\342\224\214\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\220\n\342\224\202 OpenCode | Workspace | Branch | Agent | Model | Connection | Actions  \342\224\202\n\342\224\234\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\254\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\254\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\244\n\342\224\202 Sessions      \342\224\202 Workflow summary                  \342\224\202 Workspace & Context \342\224\202\n\342\224\202               \342\224\234\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\244                     \342\224\202\n\342\224\202 Search        \342\224\202 Chat / Builder content            \342\224\202 Referenced Files    \342\224\202\n\342\224\202 New session   \342\224\202                                   \342\224\202 Modified Files      \342\224\202\n\342\224\202 Session list  \342\224\202                                   \342\224\202 Workspace Browser   \342\224\202\n\342\224\202 Status        \342\224\234\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\244 Todos               \342\224\202\n\342\224\202               \342\224\202 Composer placeholder               \342\224\202                     \342\224\202\n\342\224\224\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\264\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\264\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\230\n```\n\nAlso provide a second route for the future live preview:\n\n```text\n/live-preview\n```\n\nThe preview route must currently show a complete intentional empty state explaining that the runtime connection will be implemented in a later phase. Do not embed an iframe or start a preview server.\n\n---\n\n# Routes\n\nImplement:\n\n```text\n/               Redirect to /builder\n/builder        Chat and Builder shell\n/live-preview   Live App UI placeholder\n/*              Not-found page\n```\n\nUse React Router.\n\nThe active top-level tab must remain visually clear and keyboard accessible.\n\n---\n\n# Responsive behaviour\n\n## Desktop\n\n* Three-column layout.\n* Resizable or collapsible left and right panels.\n* Sticky top toolbar.\n* Center column receives remaining width.\n* No horizontal page overflow.\n\n## Tablet\n\n* Left sessions panel may collapse.\n* Right workspace panel may open as a drawer.\n* Center area remains usable.\n\n## Mobile\n\n* Sessions and workspace/context open as accessible drawers.\n* Main navigation remains visible.\n* Composer remains reachable.\n* No desktop-only fixed widths that break small screens.\n\nPersist panel visibility and appearance preferences through Zustand using local storage.\n\nDo not persist mock sessions or mock messages as canonical application state.\n\n---\n\n# Frontend state\n\nCreate a focused UI preference store only.\n\nSuggested state:\n\n```ts\ntype AppearanceMode = \"system\" | \"light\" | \"dark\";\ntype MainView = \"builder\" | \"live-preview\";\n\ntype UiState = {\n  appearance: AppearanceMode;\n  leftPanelOpen: boolean;\n  rightPanelOpen: boolean;\n  mobileNavigationOpen: boolean;\n  mobileContextOpen: boolean;\n  activeContextSection:\n    | \"referenced\"\n    | \"modified\"\n    | \"workspace\"\n    | \"todos\";\n};\n```\n\nRequired actions:\n\n```ts\nsetAppearance()\ntoggleLeftPanel()\ntoggleRightPanel()\nsetMobileNavigationOpen()\nsetMobileContextOpen()\nsetActiveContextSection()\nresetLayout()\n```\n\nRequirements:\n\n* Persist only interface preferences.\n* Apply system appearance changes correctly.\n* Avoid hydration flicker.\n* Do not create session, event, message, permission, or preview stores yet.\n* Do not create fake OpenCode IDs.\n\n---\n\n# Mock-data rule\n\nUse one clearly isolated module such as:\n\n```text\nsrc/mocks/frontendDemoData.ts\n```\n\nMock data exists only to demonstrate the shell.\n\nIt must contain:\n\n* Several sessions with different visible statuses\n* A small workflow timeline\n* A small message feed\n* Referenced files\n* Modified files\n* Todo items\n\nDo not mix mock data into Zustand.\n\nAdd a visible development/demo indicator so mock content cannot be mistaken for live OpenCode state.\n\nDo not create fake API delays unless they are required by a specific component test.\n\n---\n\n# Required UI states\n\nEvery remote-data-shaped region must support these visual states even though the current slice uses mock data:\n\n```ts\ntype LoadableState = \"idle\" | \"loading\" | \"ready\" | \"empty\" | \"error\";\n```\n\nBuild reusable presentation for:\n\n* Loading\n* Empty\n* Error with Retry button\n* Degraded connection\n* Ready\n\nDeterministic recovery requirements:\n\n* Opening a selector or menu must not execute any action.\n* A failed selector must retain the last valid selection when available.\n* Otherwise show a disabled retry state.\n* Never silently select an arbitrary fallback.\n* Never display repeated error notifications during rerenders.\n\n---\n\n# Main frontend components\n\nUse a maintainable component structure. The exact structure may adapt to an existing repository, but the implementation must include these responsibilities:\n\n```text\nApp\nAppRouter\nAppShell\nTopToolbar\nPrimaryNavigation\nSessionsPanel\nSessionSearch\nSessionList\nWorkflowSummary\nBuilderWorkspace\nMessageFeed\nComposerPlaceholder\nContextPanel\nLivePreviewEmptyState\nResponsiveDrawer\nErrorBoundary\nLoadablePanel\nNotFoundPage\n```\n\nDo not place the entire application in one component.\n\nDo not over-fragment simple markup into dozens of one-line components.\n\n---\n\n# Sessions panel\n\nImplement:\n\n* New Session button that is visibly disabled or demo-only\n* Search field\n* Session list\n* Active session state\n* Status indicator\n* Last activity text\n* Empty search result\n* Keyboard focus styles\n\nSession statuses displayed in this slice may include:\n\n```text\nidle\nbusy\nretrying\nattention\nerror\n```\n\nThese are visual mock states only. Do not implement OpenCode session logic.\n\n---\n\n# Top toolbar\n\nDisplay:\n\n* Product identity\n* Current workspace\n* Current branch\n* Agent selector placeholder\n* Provider/model selector placeholder\n* Connection state\n* Builder and Live Preview navigation\n* Appearance control\n* Panel toggle controls\n\nAgent and model selectors must use deterministic recovery behaviour.\n\nFor this phase they must be clearly marked as demo selectors and must not send requests.\n\n---\n\n# Workflow summary\n\nDisplay a compact timeline with examples of:\n\n* Step started\n* Tool queued\n* Tool running\n* File changed\n* Tool completed\n* Attention required\n\nDo not implement the complete Phase 12 event visualizer.\n\nThe purpose of this component is to establish layout, spacing, status language, and rendering containment.\n\nLong content must collapse rather than expanding the entire page.\n\n---\n\n# Message feed\n\nCreate a static demonstration containing:\n\n* User message\n* Assistant markdown response\n* Code block\n* Tool activity card\n* Error/retry state\n* Token and cost metadata placeholder\n\nRequirements:\n\n* Proper markdown typography\n* Selectable text\n* Copy button for code\n* Accessible labels\n* Stable scrolling container\n* No automatic scrolling that moves the user while reading older content\n* No streaming implementation yet\n* No fake SSE implementation\n* No direct API calls\n\n---\n\n# Composer placeholder\n\nCreate the complete visual composer foundation with:\n\n* Multiline textarea\n* File mention button\n* Agent mention button\n* Command button\n* Model summary\n* Send button\n* Stop button location\n* Keyboard shortcut hint\n\nCurrent behaviour:\n\n* Text entry may work locally.\n* Send must not create a real OpenCode message.\n* Either disable Send with a clear \342\200\234Gateway not connected\342\200\235 explanation or create a local visual-only demo action clearly labelled as demo.\n* Do not create browser-generated OpenCode `messageID` values.\n* Do not implement `prompt_async`.\n\n---\n\n# Workspace and context panel\n\nProvide these sections:\n\n```text\nReferenced Files\nModified Files\nWorkspace Browser\nTodos\n```\n\nRequirements:\n\n* Clear selected state\n* File icons\n* Modified-state indicators\n* Todo completion display\n* Empty states\n* Mobile drawer presentation\n* No claim that this displays the model\342\200\231s complete internal context\n* Panel title must be \342\200\234Workspace & Context\342\200\235\n\n---\n\n# Live preview route\n\nBuild a polished empty state containing:\n\n* Preview icon or illustration made with CSS/icons\n* \342\200\234Preview runtime not connected\342\200\235\n* Explanation that the local preview supervisor will be added in Phase 9\n* Disabled Start Preview button\n* Desktop, tablet, and mobile viewport selector placeholders\n* Preview logs placeholder\n* No iframe\n* No WebContainer\n* No localhost URL\n* No hardcoded preview port\n\n---\n\n# Accessibility requirements\n\nVerify:\n\n* Semantic buttons and landmarks\n* Keyboard-accessible navigation\n* Visible focus styles\n* Form labels\n* Accessible drawer controls\n* `aria-expanded` for collapsible controls\n* `aria-current` for active navigation\n* Sufficient contrast\n* No clickable non-semantic `div` elements\n* Reduced-motion support\n* No focus trapping defects in mobile drawers\n\n---\n\n# Rendering requirements\n\n* Avoid rerendering the entire shell for simple panel changes.\n* Use selectors when reading Zustand state.\n* Keep mock arrays outside render functions.\n* Use stable keys.\n* Do not create unbounded logs.\n* Collapse large mock tool output.\n* Avoid unnecessary effects.\n* Do not store derived state when it can be computed.\n* Ensure no React warnings appear in the browser console.\n\n---\n\n# Exact boundaries\n\nDo not implement:\n\n* Fastify gateway\n* Nginx\n* OpenCode server process ownership\n* `@opencode-ai/sdk`\n* API client\n* SSE or EventSource\n* Event reducer\n* Session creation API\n* `prompt_async`\n* Permission approval\n* Workspace process registry\n* SQLite\n* Preview supervisor\n* WebContainer\n* Runtime error forwarding\n* Autonomous repair\n* Authentication\n* Provider OAuth\n* PTY\n* Real file access\n* Diff or revert APIs\n\nDo not invent temporary versions of these systems.\n\nUse typed frontend interfaces only where they are needed for rendering the mock shell.\n\n---\n\n# Preferred first-batch file budget\n\nKeep the first implementation batch to approximately 12\342\200\22318 complete files.\n\nA suitable structure is:\n\n```text\napps/web/\n  package.json\n  tsconfig.json\n  tsconfig.node.json\n  vite.config.ts\n  tailwind.config.ts\n  postcss.config.cjs\n  index.html\n  src/\n    main.tsx\n    App.tsx\n    styles.css\n    components/\n      AppShell.tsx\n      ErrorBoundary.tsx\n      LoadablePanel.tsx\n    store/\n      useUiStore.ts\n    mocks/\n      frontendDemoData.ts\n    types/\n      ui.ts\n    tests/\n      app-shell.test.tsx\n      setup.ts\n```\n\nThis is guidance, not permission to overwrite repository files blindly.\n\nIf the existing repository already has equivalent files, modify them carefully rather than creating duplicates.\n\nIf this entire batch cannot be emitted completely, reduce the number of files before coding.\n\n---\n\n# A-to-Z implementation roadmap\n\n## A. Repository audit\n\n* Inspect root package files.\n* Inspect workspace configuration.\n* Detect package manager.\n* Check whether `apps/web` already exists.\n* Check current TypeScript, Tailwind, ESLint, and test setup.\n* Record findings before changing files.\n\n## B. Branch\n\nCreate:\n\n```bash\ngit switch -c feat/opencode-web-phase-1a-shell\n```\n\nIf the branch already exists, inspect it and continue only when it contains the expected task scope.\n\n## C. Frontend setup\n\nInitialize or repair the Vite React TypeScript application under `apps/web`.\n\nUse exact dependency versions compatible with the current repository.\n\nDo not use `latest`.\n\nDo not introduce a second package manager or conflicting lockfile.\n\n## D. Styling foundation\n\nConfigure Tailwind and global design tokens.\n\nInclude:\n\n* Surface hierarchy\n* Text hierarchy\n* Border hierarchy\n* Focus ring\n* Radius scale\n* Spacing rhythm\n* Light and dark appearance\n* Reduced-motion behaviour\n\nDo not hardcode the same raw colour repeatedly across components.\n\n## E. Router\n\nImplement the required routes and not-found state.\n\n## F. UI store\n\nImplement persisted interface preferences with clean Zustand selectors.\n\n## G. Shell\n\nBuild desktop, tablet, and mobile layouts.\n\n## H. Builder demonstration\n\nAdd mock sessions, timeline, message feed, composer foundation, and context panel.\n\n## I. Live preview empty state\n\nAdd the intentional Phase 9 placeholder route without implementing a runtime.\n\n## J. Recovery states\n\nImplement loading, empty, error, retry, and degraded-state presentation.\n\n## K. Accessibility\n\nComplete keyboard and semantic checks.\n\n## L. Tests\n\nAdd focused tests covering:\n\n* Builder route renders\n* Live Preview route renders\n* Navigation switches routes\n* Left panel toggles\n* Right panel toggles\n* Appearance preference changes\n* Session search filters mock sessions\n* Context section selection changes\n* Error panel exposes Retry\n* No Send action calls an API\n* Unknown route shows not-found state\n\n## M. Manifest\n\nUpdate `IMPLEMENTATION_MANIFEST.md` with:\n\n* Phase: 1\n* Slice: 1A\n* Status\n* Exact files changed\n* Dependencies added\n* Commands run\n* Tests passed\n* Known issues\n* Explicitly deferred functionality\n* Next bounded slice\n\n## N. Bug audit\n\nBefore commit, inspect for:\n\n* React key warnings\n* Invalid DOM nesting\n* Missing labels\n* Broken mobile drawers\n* Horizontal overflow\n* Theme flicker\n* State persistence failure\n* Navigation reloads\n* Search case-sensitivity defects\n* Buttons accidentally submitting forms\n* Mock selectors triggering side effects\n* Console errors\n* Duplicate lockfiles\n* Hardcoded localhost URLs\n* Direct OpenCode requests\n* Browser-generated canonical message IDs\n\n## O. Validation commands\n\nUse the repository\342\200\231s package manager.\n\nFor npm workspaces, the expected command sequence is:\n\n```bash\nnpm install\nnpm --workspace apps/web run lint\nnpm --workspace apps/web run typecheck\nnpm --workspace apps/web run test -- --run\nnpm --workspace apps/web run build\n```\n\nIf the repository uses Bun:\n\n```bash\nbun install\nbun --cwd apps/web run lint\nbun --cwd apps/web run typecheck\nbun --cwd apps/web run test\nbun --cwd apps/web run build\n```\n\nIf the repository uses pnpm:\n\n```bash\npnpm install\npnpm --filter ./apps/web lint\npnpm --filter ./apps/web typecheck\npnpm --filter ./apps/web test --run\npnpm --filter ./apps/web build\n```\n\nDo not claim a command passed unless it was actually executed.\n\n## P. Manual UI checks\n\nVerify:\n\n* `/builder` desktop layout\n* `/builder` tablet layout\n* `/builder` mobile layout\n* `/live-preview`\n* Unknown route\n* Light appearance\n* Dark appearance\n* System appearance\n* Left panel collapse\n* Right panel collapse\n* Mobile sessions drawer\n* Mobile context drawer\n* Session search\n* Context section changes\n* Keyboard-only navigation\n* Reduced-motion mode\n* Browser console has no errors\n\n## Q. Commit\n\nCommit only after all available gates pass:\n\n```bash\ngit add apps/web IMPLEMENTATION_MANIFEST.md\ngit commit -m \"feat(web): add OpenCode frontend shell foundation\"\n```\n\nDo not include unrelated files.\n\n## R. Push\n\nPush the branch:\n\n```bash\ngit push -u origin feat/opencode-web-phase-1a-shell\n```\n\nIf pull-request creation is available, create a draft PR titled:\n\n```text\nfeat(web): add OpenCode frontend shell foundation\n```\n\nThe PR description must state that this is a frontend-only foundation and that no OpenCode API integration is included.\n\n---\n\n# Completion criteria\n\nThis task is done only when:\n\n* Vite React application builds successfully.\n* Required routes work.\n* Three-panel shell is responsive.\n* Appearance preferences persist.\n* Mobile drawers work.\n* Mock data is isolated.\n* No backend or OpenCode integration was invented.\n* Tests pass.\n* Lint passes.\n* Type checking passes.\n* Production build passes.\n* Browser console has no React errors.\n* `IMPLEMENTATION_MANIFEST.md` is updated.\n* Only task-related files are committed.\n* Final implementation score is at least **9/10**.\n\nBelow 9/10 means the task is not complete.\n\n---\n\n# Required final report\n\nReturn:\n\n```text\nTask name:\nBranch:\nCommit:\nPR:\nPackage manager:\nFiles created:\nFiles modified:\nDependencies added:\nRoutes implemented:\nResponsive checks:\nAccessibility checks:\nLint:\nTypecheck:\nTests:\nBuild:\nConsole errors:\nKnown issues:\nDeferred functionality:\nManifest updated:\nFinal score:\nFinal verdict:\n```\n\nDo not begin Phase 1B, SDK integration, SSE, or preview runtime work.\n"
    items {
      text: "# Task name\n\n**OpenCode Web UI \342\200\224 Frontend Phase 1A: Production Shell and Interaction Foundation**\n\n## To me\n\n1. Paste this entire instruction into Google AI Studio.\n2. Give the builder access to the existing repository if supported.\n3. Do not ask it to build the complete application.\n4. Do not allow it to add Fastify, OpenCode SDK integration, SSE, WebContainers, preview processes, authentication, or real API calls in this task.\n5. Review the complete file batch before accepting it.\n6. The task is complete only when the final score is at least **9/10** and all available frontend gates pass.\n\n---\n\n# To dev\n\nImplement **Frontend Phase 1A only**.\n\nThis is a bounded frontend foundation slice for the OpenCode Headless Web UI. Build a polished, production-quality Vite React shell that later phases can connect to the Fastify gateway and OpenCode runtime.\n\nDo not implement Phase 2 or any backend-dependent functionality.\n\n## Atomic delivery rules\n\nBefore writing code:\n\n1. Inspect the existing repository structure.\n2. Detect the existing package manager from the repository configuration and lockfiles.\n3. List every file you will create or modify.\n4. Keep the batch small enough that every file can be emitted completely.\n5. Confirm that no file will be truncated.\n6. Do not begin a file that cannot be completed in the current response.\n\nDuring implementation:\n\n* Provide complete files.\n* Do not use placeholder comments.\n* Do not write `TODO` in place of required behaviour.\n* Do not claim a file was created unless its full content is provided or it was actually written in the repository.\n* Do not introduce backend APIs or invent OpenCode response shapes.\n* Do not start the next slice.\n\nAfter implementation:\n\n* Run all available frontend checks.\n* Update `IMPLEMENTATION_MANIFEST.md`.\n* Report exact command results.\n* Commit and push only when every required gate passes.\n* If repository execution is unavailable, output the complete files and clearly mark commands as not executed.\n\n---\n\n# Objective\n\nCreate the frontend application foundation with:\n\n* Vite\n* React\n* TypeScript\n* React Router\n* Tailwind CSS\n* Zustand\n* Lucide icons\n* Accessible reusable UI primitives\n* Responsive three-panel application shell\n* Mock data isolated from production state\n* Loading, empty, degraded, and error states\n* Dark and light appearance support\n* Keyboard-accessible navigation\n* Initial frontend tests\n\nThe UI should feel similar to a professional AI development workspace, not a generic dashboard template.\n\n---\n\n# Required visual structure\n\nBuild this desktop layout:\n\n```text\n\342\224\214\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\220\n\342\224\202 OpenCode | Workspace | Branch | Agent | Model | Connection | Actions  \342\224\202\n\342\224\234\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\254\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\254\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\244\n\342\224\202 Sessions      \342\224\202 Workflow summary                  \342\224\202 Workspace & Context \342\224\202\n\342\224\202               \342\224\234\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\244                     \342\224\202\n\342\224\202 Search        \342\224\202 Chat / Builder content            \342\224\202 Referenced Files    \342\224\202\n\342\224\202 New session   \342\224\202                                   \342\224\202 Modified Files      \342\224\202\n\342\224\202 Session list  \342\224\202                                   \342\224\202 Workspace Browser   \342\224\202\n\342\224\202 Status        \342\224\234\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\244 Todos               \342\224\202\n\342\224\202               \342\224\202 Composer placeholder               \342\224\202                     \342\224\202\n\342\224\224\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\264\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\264\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\200\342\224\230\n```\n\nAlso provide a second route for the future live preview:\n\n```text\n/live-preview\n```\n\nThe preview route must currently show a complete intentional empty state explaining that the runtime connection will be implemented in a later phase. Do not embed an iframe or start a preview server.\n\n---\n\n# Routes\n\nImplement:\n\n```text\n/               Redirect to /builder\n/builder        Chat and Builder shell\n/live-preview   Live App UI placeholder\n/*              Not-found page\n```\n\nUse React Router.\n\nThe active top-level tab must remain visually clear and keyboard accessible.\n\n---\n\n# Responsive behaviour\n\n## Desktop\n\n* Three-column layout.\n* Resizable or collapsible left and right panels.\n* Sticky top toolbar.\n* Center column receives remaining width.\n* No horizontal page overflow.\n\n## Tablet\n\n* Left sessions panel may collapse.\n* Right workspace panel may open as a drawer.\n* Center area remains usable.\n\n## Mobile\n\n* Sessions and workspace/context open as accessible drawers.\n* Main navigation remains visible.\n* Composer remains reachable.\n* No desktop-only fixed widths that break small screens.\n\nPersist panel visibility and appearance preferences through Zustand using local storage.\n\nDo not persist mock sessions or mock messages as canonical application state.\n\n---\n\n# Frontend state\n\nCreate a focused UI preference store only.\n\nSuggested state:\n\n```ts\ntype AppearanceMode = \"system\" | \"light\" | \"dark\";\ntype MainView = \"builder\" | \"live-preview\";\n\ntype UiState = {\n  appearance: AppearanceMode;\n  leftPanelOpen: boolean;\n  rightPanelOpen: boolean;\n  mobileNavigationOpen: boolean;\n  mobileContextOpen: boolean;\n  activeContextSection:\n    | \"referenced\"\n    | \"modified\"\n    | \"workspace\"\n    | \"todos\";\n};\n```\n\nRequired actions:\n\n```ts\nsetAppearance()\ntoggleLeftPanel()\ntoggleRightPanel()\nsetMobileNavigationOpen()\nsetMobileContextOpen()\nsetActiveContextSection()\nresetLayout()\n```\n\nRequirements:\n\n* Persist only interface preferences.\n* Apply system appearance changes correctly.\n* Avoid hydration flicker.\n* Do not create session, event, message, permission, or preview stores yet.\n* Do not create fake OpenCode IDs.\n\n---\n\n# Mock-data rule\n\nUse one clearly isolated module such as:\n\n```text\nsrc/mocks/frontendDemoData.ts\n```\n\nMock data exists only to demonstrate the shell.\n\nIt must contain:\n\n* Several sessions with different visible statuses\n* A small workflow timeline\n* A small message feed\n* Referenced files\n* Modified files\n* Todo items\n\nDo not mix mock data into Zustand.\n\nAdd a visible development/demo indicator so mock content cannot be mistaken for live OpenCode state.\n\nDo not create fake API delays unless they are required by a specific component test.\n\n---\n\n# Required UI states\n\nEvery remote-data-shaped region must support these visual states even though the current slice uses mock data:\n\n```ts\ntype LoadableState = \"idle\" | \"loading\" | \"ready\" | \"empty\" | \"error\";\n```\n\nBuild reusable presentation for:\n\n* Loading\n* Empty\n* Error with Retry button\n* Degraded connection\n* Ready\n\nDeterministic recovery requirements:\n\n* Opening a selector or menu must not execute any action.\n* A failed selector must retain the last valid selection when available.\n* Otherwise show a disabled retry state.\n* Never silently select an arbitrary fallback.\n* Never display repeated error notifications during rerenders.\n\n---\n\n# Main frontend components\n\nUse a maintainable component structure. The exact structure may adapt to an existing repository, but the implementation must include these responsibilities:\n\n```text\nApp\nAppRouter\nAppShell\nTopToolbar\nPrimaryNavigation\nSessionsPanel\nSessionSearch\nSessionList\nWorkflowSummary\nBuilderWorkspace\nMessageFeed\nComposerPlaceholder\nContextPanel\nLivePreviewEmptyState\nResponsiveDrawer\nErrorBoundary\nLoadablePanel\nNotFoundPage\n```\n\nDo not place the entire application in one component.\n\nDo not over-fragment simple markup into dozens of one-line components.\n\n---\n\n# Sessions panel\n\nImplement:\n\n* New Session button that is visibly disabled or demo-only\n* Search field\n* Session list\n* Active session state\n* Status indicator\n* Last activity text\n* Empty search result\n* Keyboard focus styles\n\nSession statuses displayed in this slice may include:\n\n```text\nidle\nbusy\nretrying\nattention\nerror\n```\n\nThese are visual mock states only. Do not implement OpenCode session logic.\n\n---\n\n# Top toolbar\n\nDisplay:\n\n* Product identity\n* Current workspace\n* Current branch\n* Agent selector placeholder\n* Provider/model selector placeholder\n* Connection state\n* Builder and Live Preview navigation\n* Appearance control\n* Panel toggle controls\n\nAgent and model selectors must use deterministic recovery behaviour.\n\nFor this phase they must be clearly marked as demo selectors and must not send requests.\n\n---\n\n# Workflow summary\n\nDisplay a compact timeline with examples of:\n\n* Step started\n* Tool queued\n* Tool running\n* File changed\n* Tool completed\n* Attention required\n\nDo not implement the complete Phase 12 event visualizer.\n\nThe purpose of this component is to establish layout, spacing, status language, and rendering containment.\n\nLong content must collapse rather than expanding the entire page.\n\n---\n\n# Message feed\n\nCreate a static demonstration containing:\n\n* User message\n* Assistant markdown response\n* Code block\n* Tool activity card\n* Error/retry state\n* Token and cost metadata placeholder\n\nRequirements:\n\n* Proper markdown typography\n* Selectable text\n* Copy button for code\n* Accessible labels\n* Stable scrolling container\n* No automatic scrolling that moves the user while reading older content\n* No streaming implementation yet\n* No fake SSE implementation\n* No direct API calls\n\n---\n\n# Composer placeholder\n\nCreate the complete visual composer foundation with:\n\n* Multiline textarea\n* File mention button\n* Agent mention button\n* Command button\n* Model summary\n* Send button\n* Stop button location\n* Keyboard shortcut hint\n\nCurrent behaviour:\n\n* Text entry may work locally.\n* Send must not create a real OpenCode message.\n* Either disable Send with a clear \342\200\234Gateway not connected\342\200\235 explanation or create a local visual-only demo action clearly labelled as demo.\n* Do not create browser-generated OpenCode `messageID` values.\n* Do not implement `prompt_async`.\n\n---\n\n# Workspace and context panel\n\nProvide these sections:\n\n```text\nReferenced Files\nModified Files\nWorkspace Browser\nTodos\n```\n\nRequirements:\n\n* Clear selected state\n* File icons\n* Modified-state indicators\n* Todo completion display\n* Empty states\n* Mobile drawer presentation\n* No claim that this displays the model\342\200\231s complete internal context\n* Panel title must be \342\200\234Workspace & Context\342\200\235\n\n---\n\n# Live preview route\n\nBuild a polished empty state containing:\n\n* Preview icon or illustration made with CSS/icons\n* \342\200\234Preview runtime not connected\342\200\235\n* Explanation that the local preview supervisor will be added in Phase 9\n* Disabled Start Preview button\n* Desktop, tablet, and mobile viewport selector placeholders\n* Preview logs placeholder\n* No iframe\n* No WebContainer\n* No localhost URL\n* No hardcoded preview port\n\n---\n\n# Accessibility requirements\n\nVerify:\n\n* Semantic buttons and landmarks\n* Keyboard-accessible navigation\n* Visible focus styles\n* Form labels\n* Accessible drawer controls\n* `aria-expanded` for collapsible controls\n* `aria-current` for active navigation\n* Sufficient contrast\n* No clickable non-semantic `div` elements\n* Reduced-motion support\n* No focus trapping defects in mobile drawers\n\n---\n\n# Rendering requirements\n\n* Avoid rerendering the entire shell for simple panel changes.\n* Use selectors when reading Zustand state.\n* Keep mock arrays outside render functions.\n* Use stable keys.\n* Do not create unbounded logs.\n* Collapse large mock tool output.\n* Avoid unnecessary effects.\n* Do not store derived state when it can be computed.\n* Ensure no React warnings appear in the browser console.\n\n---\n\n# Exact boundaries\n\nDo not implement:\n\n* Fastify gateway\n* Nginx\n* OpenCode server process ownership\n* `@opencode-ai/sdk`\n* API client\n* SSE or EventSource\n* Event reducer\n* Session creation API\n* `prompt_async`\n* Permission approval\n* Workspace process registry\n* SQLite\n* Preview supervisor\n* WebContainer\n* Runtime error forwarding\n* Autonomous repair\n* Authentication\n* Provider OAuth\n* PTY\n* Real file access\n* Diff or revert APIs\n\nDo not invent temporary versions of these systems.\n\nUse typed frontend interfaces only where they are needed for rendering the mock shell.\n\n---\n\n# Preferred first-batch file budget\n\nKeep the first implementation batch to approximately 12\342\200\22318 complete files.\n\nA suitable structure is:\n\n```text\napps/web/\n  package.json\n  tsconfig.json\n  tsconfig.node.json\n  vite.config.ts\n  tailwind.config.ts\n  postcss.config.cjs\n  index.html\n  src/\n    main.tsx\n    App.tsx\n    styles.css\n    components/\n      AppShell.tsx\n      ErrorBoundary.tsx\n      LoadablePanel.tsx\n    store/\n      useUiStore.ts\n    mocks/\n      frontendDemoData.ts\n    types/\n      ui.ts\n    tests/\n      app-shell.test.tsx\n      setup.ts\n```\n\nThis is guidance, not permission to overwrite repository files blindly.\n\nIf the existing repository already has equivalent files, modify them carefully rather than creating duplicates.\n\nIf this entire batch cannot be emitted completely, reduce the number of files before coding.\n\n---\n\n# A-to-Z implementation roadmap\n\n## A. Repository audit\n\n* Inspect root package files.\n* Inspect workspace configuration.\n* Detect package manager.\n* Check whether `apps/web` already exists.\n* Check current TypeScript, Tailwind, ESLint, and test setup.\n* Record findings before changing files.\n\n## B. Branch\n\nCreate:\n\n```bash\ngit switch -c feat/opencode-web-phase-1a-shell\n```\n\nIf the branch already exists, inspect it and continue only when it contains the expected task scope.\n\n## C. Frontend setup\n\nInitialize or repair the Vite React TypeScript application under `apps/web`.\n\nUse exact dependency versions compatible with the current repository.\n\nDo not use `latest`.\n\nDo not introduce a second package manager or conflicting lockfile.\n\n## D. Styling foundation\n\nConfigure Tailwind and global design tokens.\n\nInclude:\n\n* Surface hierarchy\n* Text hierarchy\n* Border hierarchy\n* Focus ring\n* Radius scale\n* Spacing rhythm\n* Light and dark appearance\n* Reduced-motion behaviour\n\nDo not hardcode the same raw colour repeatedly across components.\n\n## E. Router\n\nImplement the required routes and not-found state.\n\n## F. UI store\n\nImplement persisted interface preferences with clean Zustand selectors.\n\n## G. Shell\n\nBuild desktop, tablet, and mobile layouts.\n\n## H. Builder demonstration\n\nAdd mock sessions, timeline, message feed, composer foundation, and context panel.\n\n## I. Live preview empty state\n\nAdd the intentional Phase 9 placeholder route without implementing a runtime.\n\n## J. Recovery states\n\nImplement loading, empty, error, retry, and degraded-state presentation.\n\n## K. Accessibility\n\nComplete keyboard and semantic checks.\n\n## L. Tests\n\nAdd focused tests covering:\n\n* Builder route renders\n* Live Preview route renders\n* Navigation switches routes\n* Left panel toggles\n* Right panel toggles\n* Appearance preference changes\n* Session search filters mock sessions\n* Context section selection changes\n* Error panel exposes Retry\n* No Send action calls an API\n* Unknown route shows not-found state\n\n## M. Manifest\n\nUpdate `IMPLEMENTATION_MANIFEST.md` with:\n\n* Phase: 1\n* Slice: 1A\n* Status\n* Exact files changed\n* Dependencies added\n* Commands run\n* Tests passed\n* Known issues\n* Explicitly deferred functionality\n* Next bounded slice\n\n## N. Bug audit\n\nBefore commit, inspect for:\n\n* React key warnings\n* Invalid DOM nesting\n* Missing labels\n* Broken mobile drawers\n* Horizontal overflow\n* Theme flicker\n* State persistence failure\n* Navigation reloads\n* Search case-sensitivity defects\n* Buttons accidentally submitting forms\n* Mock selectors triggering side effects\n* Console errors\n* Duplicate lockfiles\n* Hardcoded localhost URLs\n* Direct OpenCode requests\n* Browser-generated canonical message IDs\n\n## O. Validation commands\n\nUse the repository\342\200\231s package manager.\n\nFor npm workspaces, the expected command sequence is:\n\n```bash\nnpm install\nnpm --workspace apps/web run lint\nnpm --workspace apps/web run typecheck\nnpm --workspace apps/web run test -- --run\nnpm --workspace apps/web run build\n```\n\nIf the repository uses Bun:\n\n```bash\nbun install\nbun --cwd apps/web run lint\nbun --cwd apps/web run typecheck\nbun --cwd apps/web run test\nbun --cwd apps/web run build\n```\n\nIf the repository uses pnpm:\n\n```bash\npnpm install\npnpm --filter ./apps/web lint\npnpm --filter ./apps/web typecheck\npnpm --filter ./apps/web test --run\npnpm --filter ./apps/web build\n```\n\nDo not claim a command passed unless it was actually executed.\n\n## P. Manual UI checks\n\nVerify:\n\n* `/builder` desktop layout\n* `/builder` tablet layout\n* `/builder` mobile layout\n* `/live-preview`\n* Unknown route\n* Light appearance\n* Dark appearance\n* System appearance\n* Left panel collapse\n* Right panel collapse\n* Mobile sessions drawer\n* Mobile context drawer\n* Session search\n* Context section changes\n* Keyboard-only navigation\n* Reduced-motion mode\n* Browser console has no errors\n\n## Q. Commit\n\nCommit only after all available gates pass:\n\n```bash\ngit add apps/web IMPLEMENTATION_MANIFEST.md\ngit commit -m \"feat(web): add OpenCode frontend shell foundation\"\n```\n\nDo not include unrelated files.\n\n## R. Push\n\nPush the branch:\n\n```bash\ngit push -u origin feat/opencode-web-phase-1a-shell\n```\n\nIf pull-request creation is available, create a draft PR titled:\n\n```text\nfeat(web): add OpenCode frontend shell foundation\n```\n\nThe PR description must state that this is a frontend-only foundation and that no OpenCode API integration is included.\n\n---\n\n# Completion criteria\n\nThis task is done only when:\n\n* Vite React application builds successfully.\n* Required routes work.\n* Three-panel shell is responsive.\n* Appearance preferences persist.\n* Mobile drawers work.\n* Mock data is isolated.\n* No backend or OpenCode integration was invented.\n* Tests pass.\n* Lint passes.\n* Type checking passes.\n* Production build passes.\n* Browser console has no React errors.\n* `IMPLEMENTATION_MANIFEST.md` is updated.\n* Only task-related files are committed.\n* Final implementation score is at least **9/10**.\n\nBelow 9/10 means the task is not complete.\n\n---\n\n# Required final report\n\nReturn:\n\n```text\nTask name:\nBranch:\nCommit:\nPR:\nPackage manager:\nFiles created:\nFiles modified:\nDependencies added:\nRoutes implemented:\nResponsive checks:\nAccessibility checks:\nLint:\nTypecheck:\nTests:\nBuild:\nConsole errors:\nKnown issues:\nDeferred functionality:\nManifest updated:\nFinal score:\nFinal verdict:\n```\n\nDo not begin Phase 1B, SDK integration, SSE, or preview runtime work.\n"
    }
  }
}
