  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Planning the Architecture**\n\nI\'m carefully reviewing all requirements of the prompt for the OpenCode Web UI\'s frontend Phase 1A. My focus is entirely on meticulously planning the architecture.\n\n\n**Defining the Constraints**\n\nI\'ve nailed down the rigid constraints of Phase 1A for the OpenCode UI frontend. No Fastify, SDK, or real API calls are allowed yet. I\'m focusing on fully written, functional code with a clean component structure and a meticulous `IMPLEMENTATION_MANIFEST.md`. The design also specifies zero code truncation.\n\n\n**Detailing the Interface**\n\nI\'m now detailing the user interface\'s finer points. I\'m prioritizing deterministic agent/model selectors for a robust user experience. The left panel design includes session list features, while the center column lays out workflow summaries and the builder workspace, with messages and composer placeholders. I\'m focusing on features such as stable scroll containers and error handling in the workflow.\n\n\n**Specifying the Controls**\n\nI\'m currently specifying UI controls: file, agent, and command mentions, a model summary, and send/stop buttons with specific states. Keyboard shortcut hints are crucial. I\'m prioritizing the \"Workspace & Context\" panel, including file references, modifications, a browser, and a to-do list with selected state indicators, icons, and empty states. I\'m focusing on fully responsive behavior across desktop, tablet, and mobile, with persistent preferences in Zustand\'s localStorage. I\'m working on accessible UI elements, including `aria` attributes.\n\n\n**Defining the Store**\n\nI\'m now defining the UI store. I\'ve sketched the `AppearanceMode`, `MainView`, and `ContextSection` types. I\'m focusing on UI states, like appearance and panel visibility. I\'m working on the data structure for the UI with methods to manage the state. Also, I\'m making sure mock data for sessions and workflows is isolated to prevent mixing into the canonical state.\n\n\n**Detailing the Interface**\n\nI\'m now detailing the message list\'s format. I\'m focusing on user messages, agent responses, markdown display, and code snippets, plus tool invocation cards with cost and token metadata. I\'m thinking about including referenced files, modifications, workspace tree, and a to-do list for context. I\'ll need a demo mode banner.\n\n**Defining the UI States**\n\nI\'m developing UI states, starting with `LoadableState = \"idle\" | \"loading\" | \"ready\" | \"empty\" | \"error\"`. I need to work on error presentation with a Retry button, plus empty-state rendering and degraded state handling.\n\n**Improving the Design**\n\nI am now focused on accessibility and design. I\'m implementing a dark and light theme with Tailwind and CSS variables, and building a high-quality typographic hierarchy with proper padding and focus rings. I\'ll use semantic HTML tags. I\'m adding `aria-expanded` and `aria-current=\"page\"`.\n\n\n**Listing the Files**\n\nI\'ve enumerated all files required for the project, ensuring a meticulous and thorough approach without shortcuts or truncation. I\'m starting by creating `IMPLEMENTATION_MANIFEST.md` to guide the implementation.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 9
      nanos: 221162980
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
